Egypt Stocks: Orascom Development and Six of October Development

-- B y   A h m e d   A .   N a m a t a l l a
-- 
2011-08-29T12:37:44Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-29/egypt-stocks-orascom-development-and-six-of-october-development.html
Egypt ’s benchmark  EGX 30 Index (EGX30) 
retreated 0.2 percent to 4,639.64 at the 1:30 p.m. close in
Cairo, the the lowest level in almost a week. The measure fell
7.9 percent this month. Egypt’s bourse is closed for the rest of
the week for a holiday.  The following shares rose or fell. Symbols are in
Parentheses.  Orascom Development Holding AG (ODHN)   tumbled 8.7
percent to 7.03 Egyptian pounds, the lowest level since
Bloomberg started tracking the company’s Egyptian depository
receipts in December 2009. Samih Sawiris, chairman of the
Altdorf, Switzerland-based resorts developer, was sentenced to
two years in jail, a fine of 6,780 Swiss francs ($8,334), and
bail of 2,720 francs over disclosure violations, the company
said in a statement today. Orascom Development filed an appeal
against the judgment and initiated discussions about a
settlement.  Six of October Development & Investment (OCDI)  Co rose
for the first time in three days, gaining 1.1 percent to 17.18
pounds. The Cairo-based luxury real-estate developer will buy
back 1 million shares at 18 pounds each from today until Sept.
14.  To contact the reporter on this story:
